HUNT
====

Hunt is small text adventure game written in standard C99 for fun. It uses its
own command line which recognizes specific commands. The adventure takes place
in a jungle and your target is to capture as many animals as you can. For each
animal you capture, you earn gold and gain some xp. You can buy bullets, better
weapons and drugs in case you get hurt by an animal.

Requirements
------------
You only need a C compiler and the Make tool.

Installation
-------------
Just type make to compile the program.

You can remove the program binaries and object files from the source code
directory by typing `make clean'.
